        <li>Original graphics</li>
        <li>Original layout elements</li>
        <li>Original photos or videos</li>
        <li>Compilations</li>
        <li>Design elements</li>
        <li>Original commentary</li>
        <li>Original summaries and analysis</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Third-party content remains the property of its respective owners.</p>
      <h3>Public-interest reporting and fair use</h3>
      <p>ShadabChow.com may publish, quote, embed, reference, summarize, comment on, or link to third-party material for purposes such as news reporting, criticism, commentary, public accountability, public-interest analysis, education, or context.</p>
      <p>Depending on the circumstances, some uses may be protected by fair use, fair dealing, license, permission, public-domain status, public-record status, platform embedding rules, or other legal principles.</p>
      <p>Examples may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Quoting a short excerpt for commentary</li>
        <li>Embedding a public social media post</li>
        <li>Referencing a public document</li>
        <li>Showing a limited screenshot for news context</li>
        <li>Discussing a public statement</li>
        <li>Reporting on a video or image that is itself newsworthy</li>
        <li>Using a thumbnail or cropped image to identify a public-interest story</li>
      </ul>
      <p>A copyright complaint does not automatically mean content will be removed. The site may review the claim, context, public-interest value, source, usage, amount used, and applicable legal considerations.</p>
      <h3>Submitted photos, videos, and documents</h3>
      <p>Readers, sources, witnesses, and community members may submit photos, videos, documents, screenshots, links, or other materials.</p>
      <p>By submitting material, you represent that:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You have the right to submit it</li>
        <li>The material does not violate copyright law</li>
        <li>The material does not violate another person’s rights</li>
        <li>The material was not obtained unlawfully</li>
        <li>The material does not include illegal or prohibited content</li>
        <li>The material may be reviewed for possible editorial use</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Submitting material does not guarantee publication, payment, credit, confidentiality, legal protection, or a response.</p>
      <p>Do not submit copyrighted material that you do not own or do not have permission or legal basis to share.</p>
      <h3>Embedded third-party content</h3>
      <p>Articles may include embedded content from third-party platforms, such as videos, social media posts, documents, maps, or other media.</p>
      <p>Embedded content may be hosted by the third-party platform, not by ShadabChow.com.</p>
      <p>If you believe embedded content infringes your rights, you may contact the platform hosting the material in addition to contacting ShadabChow.com.</p>
      <p>The site may remove or replace embedded material when appropriate, but it may not control the underlying third-party platform.</p>
      <h3>Copyright complaint process</h3>
      <p>If you believe material on ShadabChow.com infringes your copyright, submit a copyright complaint with enough information for review.</p>
      <p>Your complaint should include:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Your full legal name</li>
        <li>Your organization, if applicable</li>
        <li>Your email address</li>
        <li>Your phone number, if available</li>
        <li>Identification of the copyrighted work you claim was infringed</li>
        <li>The URL of the allegedly infringing material on ShadabChow.com</li>
        <li>A description of where the allegedly infringing material appears on the page</li>
        <li>A statement explaining your ownership or authorization to act for the copyright owner</li>
        <li>A statement explaining why you believe the use is unauthorized</li>
        <li>Any relevant registration number, source URL, publication date, or proof of ownership</li>
        <li>A statement that the information in your complaint is accurate</li>
        <li>Your physical or electronic signature</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Incomplete complaints may be difficult to review.</p>
      <h3>Suggested complaint statement</h3>
      <p>You may include this statement in your complaint:</p>
      <pre><code>I have a good-faith belief that the use of the copyrighted material identified in this notice is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law. I state that the information in this notice is accurate, and that I am the copyright owner or authorized to act on behalf of the copyright owner.</code></pre>
      <h3>Where to send a copyright complaint</h3>
      <p>Use the Contact page unless a dedicated copyright email is later provided.</p>
      <p>Recommended contact path:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact page: <code>/pages/contact</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p>When submitting a copyright complaint, include Copyright Complaint or DMCA Notice in the subject or first line of your message.</p>
      <h3>Review of copyright complaints</h3>
      <p>After receiving a copyright complaint, ShadabChow.com may:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Review the material</li>
        <li>Request more information</li>
        <li>Remove the material</li>
        <li>Disable access to the material</li>
        <li>Replace the material</li>
        <li>Add attribution or context</li>
        <li>Determine the use is permitted</li>
        <li>Decline an incomplete or unsupported complaint</li>
        <li>Forward the complaint to a contributor, source, host, service provider, or legal advisor</li>
        <li>Preserve records related to the dispute</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The site may act quickly in some cases and may take more time in others, depending on complexity, urgency, legal risk, and available evidence.</p>
      <h3>Counter-notices</h3>
      <p>If material you submitted or own was removed because of a copyright complaint and you believe the removal was mistaken, you may submit a counter-notice where applicable.</p>
      <p>A counter-notice should include:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Your full legal name</li>
        <li>Your contact information</li>
        <li>Identification of the removed material</li>
        <li>The URL where the material appeared before removal, if available</li>
        <li>A statement explaining why you believe the material was removed by mistake or misidentification</li>
        <li>A statement that you consent to the jurisdiction required by applicable law, if applicable</li>
        <li>A statement that the information in your counter-notice is accurate</li>
        <li>Your physical or electronic signature</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Do not submit a counter-notice unless you understand the legal consequences. Consider speaking with an attorney before submitting one.</p>
      <h3>Repeat infringement</h3>
      <p>ShadabChow.com may restrict, block, remove, or decline submissions from users, contributors, sources, advertisers, or accounts that repeatedly submit infringing material or abusive copyright claims.</p>
      <p>The site may also remove repeat infringer access where appropriate.</p>
      <h3>False or abusive claims</h3>
      <p>Do not submit false, misleading, abusive, or bad-faith copyright complaints.</p>
      <p>Misusing the copyright complaint process can harm lawful reporting, commentary, criticism, public accountability, and fair use.</p>
      <p>False claims may result in rejection of the request, publication of clarifying information, legal exposure, or restriction from future submissions.</p>
      <h3>News reporting and takedown requests</h3>
      <p>A request to remove content because it is embarrassing, critical, negative, newsworthy, controversial, or unfavorable is not the same as a copyright complaint.</p>
      <p>For factual errors, privacy concerns, outdated information, or public-interest takedown requests, use the Corrections Policy or Contact page.</p>
      <p>Copyright complaints should identify specific copyrighted material and explain the claimed infringement.</p>
      <h3>Attribution requests</h3>
      <p>If you believe material should include additional attribution, contact the site with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The article URL</li>
        <li>The relevant image, video, quote, document, or source</li>
        <li>The requested attribution</li>
        <li>Supporting proof or source link</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The site may add, update, or decline attribution based on editorial judgment, legal considerations, source reliability, and available evidence.</p>
      <h3>Use of ShadabChow.com content</h3>
      <p>You may link to public pages on ShadabChow.com.</p>
      <p>You may quote short excerpts for commentary, criticism, news discussion, or fair-use purposes where permitted by law, with appropriate attribution and a link when possible.</p>
      <p>You may not copy, scrape, mirror, sell, republish, or redistribute substantial portions of the site without permission, except where allowed by law.</p>
      <h3>Advertising and copyright</h3>
      <p>Advertising, sponsorship, donations, or business relationships do not control copyright decisions.</p>
      <p>Advertisers, sponsors, donors, vendors, and partners do not receive the right to force removal of public-interest reporting through copyright claims.</p>
      <p>Do not click, view, refresh, or interact with ads as part of a copyright complaint, copyright request, takedown request, or ownership dispute.</p>
      <h3>Privacy and personal information in complaints</h3>
      <p>Copyright complaints may include personal information such as name, organization, email address, phone number, signature, and claim details.</p>
      <p>This information may be used to review the claim, communicate with parties, preserve records, respond to legal requirements, contact service providers, or process disputes.</p>
      <p>For more information, review the Privacy Policy.</p>
      <h3>Changes to this policy</h3>
      <p>This Copyright / DMCA Policy may be updated from time to time.</p>
      <p>When updates are made, the effective date may change. Continued use of the site after changes means you accept the updated policy.</p>
      <h3>Contact</h3>
      <p>For copyright complaints or questions, use the Contact page.</p>
